sources.title: Come on, Cowboys
sources.description: Harris (Anne Bennett) and Rigby (Edward Peil Jr.) own a circus. Rigby is a counterfeiter and frames his partner. The Mesquiteers learn Rigby is the culprit and get a confession from one of his men only to lose the case when the man is murdered in jail. The Mesquiteers try again and send Lullaby (Max Terhune) to try and win some of the fake bills in a card game.

sources.title: Come on, Cowboys (1937) Fake money, real danger: How the West was swindled - by Joseph Kane
sources.description:
The Three Mesquiteers (Robert Livingston, Ray Corrigan, Max Terhune) uncover fake money at a traveling circus and vow to protect a little girl after her father is framed by his partner. With custody hinging on a rushed wedding, they stage a clever sting—complete with a costumed scare and a runaway buckboard—to expose the forger and clear the dad.

Directed by Joseph Kane
